title="Marcelo Fiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Under the correspondence between boolean <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00IS.xml"
addr="jms-00IS"
title="Matrix over a semiring">matrices</fr:link> and finite <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00I7.xml"
addr="jms-00I7"
title="Relation">relations</fr:link> (<fr:ref
addr="jms-00J1"
href="jms-00J1.xml" />, <fr:ref
addr="jms-00IX"
href="jms-00IX.xml"
taxon="Lemma" />), <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00IV.xml"
addr="jms-00IV"
title="Product of matrices">matrix products</fr:link> of boolean <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00IS.xml"
addr="jms-00IS"
title="Matrix over a semiring">matrices</fr:link> correspond to <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00IN.xml"
addr="jms-00IN"
title="Relational composite">relational composites</fr:link>. In particular, given <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M\in \mathrm {Mat}_{\mathbb {B}}{\mathopen {}\left (l,m\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[N\in \mathrm {Mat}_{\mathbb {B}}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, we have:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[  \operatorname {\underline {rel}}_\mathbb {B}{\mathopen {}\left (N\cdot  M\right )\mathclose {}} = \operatorname {\underline {rel}}_\mathbb {B} N\circ  \operatorname {\underline {rel}}_\mathbb {B} M ]]></fr:tex>
 
   
